description: Live performances from local and national artists across multiple genres including rock, jazz, folk, and electronic music. This day-long festival features three stages with continuous performances, food trucks offering cuisines from around the world, craft beer gardens, artisan market stalls, and interactive art installations. Family-friendly activities will be available in the designated kids' zone, including face painting and instrument-making workshops. Early bird tickets are available now with special discounts for students, seniors, and groups of 5 or more people.
title: Summer Music Festival

description: Deep dive into state management and performance optimization strategies for complex React applications. This 2-hour technical webinar will explore advanced hooks usage, context API best practices, state management libraries comparison (Redux vs MobX vs Recoil), code splitting techniques, lazy loading implementation, memoization strategies, and effective component composition patterns. The session will include live coding demonstrations, optimization benchmarks, and practical tips for refactoring existing applications. Attendees will receive access to code repositories, reference materials, and a recording of the webinar. Some experience with React is recommended to get the most value from this advanced session.
title: React.js Advanced Techniques Webinar
